					<div class="text_overlay m-bottom-0">
						<h3>The top four: A handful of giant companies control more than half the market</h3>
						<hr/>
						<p>A handful of companies have come to dominate both the poultry market and the supply chain.</p>
						<p>Today, the top four chicken companies—Tyson Foods, Pilgrim’s, Perdue, and Sanderson Farms—control roughly 60 percent of the market. They have extraordinary control over the production process and the market. And they set the pace for the rest of the industry, including workforce practices.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
