				<div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
					<div class="text_overlay">
						<p>In the past 60 years, the poultry business has become an industrial powerhouse dominated by a handful of companies. The chicken factory of today has one urgent imperative: to take all the live birds that are delivered at the entrance, and process them into chicken products that ship out the exit. </p>
						<p>Workers are part of this complex machine, and the industry puts pressure on them to work as cheaply, quickly, and quietly as possible.</p>
